      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Indoor photograph of a deathbed of a man, surrounded by flowers, wreaths and candles. An icon is laid on top of the white coverlet over him.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Dimitar Nikolov Petkov (1858 - 1907) was a Bulgarian publicist and politician, Mayor of Sofia (1888 - 1893), leading member of the Bulgarian People's Liberal Party and the country's Prime Minister from November 5, 1906 until he was assassinated in Sofia on March 11, 1907.</ab>
